display="block">         w \colon   \mathbb {G}_ \mathrm {m} \to  S       \tag{2.1.3.1}       </fr:tex></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>

    
    that, on the real points, induces the inclusion of <fr:tex>\mathbb {R} ^*</fr:tex> into <fr:tex>\mathbb {C} ^*</fr:tex>.
    We have

    <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="false"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>779</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:addr>hodge-theory-ii-2.1.3.2</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-ii-2.1.3.2.xml</fr:route><fr:number>2.1.3.2</fr:number><fr:parent>hodge-theory-ii-2.1.3</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex
display="block">         zw         =  \bar {z}w         =  \mathrm {Id} .       \tag{2.1.3.2}       </fr:tex></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:p><fr:p>
    We also have a map

    <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="false"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
